Package org.eclipse.mosaic.lib.util.scheduling

Class Event

java.lang.Object
org.eclipse.mosaic.lib.util.scheduling.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Event>
Direct Known Subclasses:
InterceptedEvent
@Immutable public class Event extends Object implements Comparable<Event>
Information to be processed at a simulation point is called event. The event requires at least a time and a processor. The event can optionally hold a priority and a resource.

    • Event

      public Event(long time, @Nonnull EventProcessor processor, @Nullable Object resource, long nice)
      Constructor for convenience.
      Parameters:
      time - The simulation time to execute this event. Unit: [ns].
      processor - The processor, which should execute the event.
      resource - The resource to process.
      nice - The niceness of this event in natural order. Low niceness means a high priority. A high niceness means a low priority.
